Liver and Kidney Damage
Many pain medications can cause liver and kidney damage over time…
Acetaminophen (Tylenol) is one of the most common pain relievers that
can cause liver damage, while…ibuprofen and aspirin can cause kidney
damage.
Long-term use of pain medications like NSAIDs can also cause stomach
and digestive problems - ulcers, bleeding, and gastrointestinal irritation.
These side effects can be particularly dangerous for people who are
already at high risk for gastrointestinal problems, such as older adults or
those with a history of ulcers or other digestive issues.
Stomach and Digestive Problems
Risk of Addiction and Overdose
Long-term use of opioid pain medications can lead to addiction and
dependence, increasing the risk of overdose. Opioids can also cause
respiratory depression, a potentially life-threatening condition where
breathing becomes slow and shallow.
